03/03/2003
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- The international community vowed continued support for reforming the public administration of Macedonia, during a conference Friday (28 February) in Skopje. 
It marked the completion of the first stage of a project to enhance the capacity of public servants, conducted with the British government. 
Stage two begins next month and will last three years. 
Macedonian Deputy Prime Minister Radmila Sekerinska noted that one goal is to create an effective, transparent and professional state administration, fully capable of managing the process of EU membership. 
(Utrinski Vesnik - 03/03/03; Makfax - 28/02/03)
